body_html:
I think DataType 21 is DT_VARIANT, which is indeed the expected dtype for a TextLineDataset:

tensorflow/tensorflow/core/framework/types.proto

Line 37 in ab0fcac

DT_VARIANT = 21; // Arbitrary C++ data types

I'm not sure why it's not supported in the Go API, but there is a TODO here:

tensorflow/tensorflow/go/tensor.go

Line 237 in ab0fcac

// TODO(keveman): support DT_VARIANT representation in go.

Since I believe @keveman is busy with other things ;), I'm reassigning this to @asimshankar who owns the Go API.

body:
I think `DataType 21` is `DT_VARIANT`, which is indeed the expected dtype for a `TextLineDataset`:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/ab0fcaceda001825654424bf18e8a8e0f8d39df2/tensorflow/core/framework/types.proto#L37

I'm not sure why it's not supported in the Go API, but there is a TODO here:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/ab0fcaceda001825654424bf18e8a8e0f8d39df2/tensorflow/go/tensor.go#L237

Since I believe @keveman is busy with other things ;), I'm reassigning this to @asimshankar who owns the Go API.
